ciscoIetfAtm2PvctrapMIB.name: ciscoIetfAtm2PvctrapMIB
ciscoIetfAtm2PvctrapMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-atm@cisco.com
ciscoIetfAtm2PvctrapMIB.description: This MIB Module is a supplement to the ATM-MIB.

atmInterfaceExtTable.name: atmInterfaceExtTable
atmInterfaceExtTable.description: This table contains ATM interface monitoring information not defined in the atmInterfaceConfTable from the ATM-MIB.

atmInterfaceExtEntry.name: atmInterfaceExtEntry
atmInterfaceExtEntry.description: An entry extends the atmInterfaceConfEntry defined in ATM MIB. Each entry corresponds to an ATM interface.

atmIntfPvcFailures.name: atmIntfPvcFailures
atmIntfPvcFailures.description: The number of times the operational status of a PVCL on this interface has gone down.

atmIntfCurrentlyFailingPVcls.name: atmIntfCurrentlyFailingPVcls
atmIntfCurrentlyFailingPVcls.description: The current number of VCLs on this interface for which there is an active row in the atmVclTable having an atmVclConnKind value of `pvc' and an atmVclOperStatus with a value other than `up'.

atmIntfPvcFailuresTrapEnable.name: atmIntfPvcFailuresTrapEnable
atmIntfPvcFailuresTrapEnable.description: Allows the generation of traps in response to PVCL failures on this interface.

atmIntfPvcNotificationInterval.name: atmIntfPvcNotificationInterval
atmIntfPvcNotificationInterval.description: The minimum interval between the sending of cIntfPvcFailuresTrap notifications for this interface.

atmPreviouslyFailedPVclInterval.name: atmPreviouslyFailedPVclInterval
atmPreviouslyFailedPVclInterval.description: The interval for storing the failed time in atmPreviouslyFailedPVclTimeStamp

atmCurrentlyFailingPVclTable.name: atmCurrentlyFailingPVclTable
atmCurrentlyFailingPVclTable.description: A table indicating all VCLs for which there is an active row in the atmVclTable having an atmVclConnKind value of `pvc' and an atmVclOperStatus with a value other than `up'.

atmCurrentlyFailingPVclEntry.name: atmCurrentlyFailingPVclEntry
atmCurrentlyFailingPVclEntry.description: Each entry in this table represents a VCL for which the atmVclRowStatus is `active', the atmVclConnKind is `pvc', and the atmVclOperStatus is other than `up'.

atmCurrentlyFailingPVclTimeStamp.name: atmCurrentlyFailingPVclTimeStamp
atmCurrentlyFailingPVclTimeStamp.description: The time at which this PVCL began to fail.

atmPreviouslyFailedPVclTimeStamp.name: atmPreviouslyFailedPVclTimeStamp
atmPreviouslyFailedPVclTimeStamp.description: The time at which this PVCL began to fail during the PVC Notification interval.

atmIntfPvcFailuresTrap.name: atmIntfPvcFailuresTrap
atmIntfPvcFailuresTrap.description: A notification indicating that one or more PVCLs on this interface has failed since the last cIntfPvcFailuresTrap was sent. If this trap has not been sent for the last cIntfPvcNotificationInterval, then it will be sent on the next increment of cIntfPvcFailures.

atm2MIBCompliance.name: atm2MIBCompliance
atm2MIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for SNMP entities which implement PVC traps.

atmSwitchServcHostGroup.name: atmSwitchServcHostGroup
atmSwitchServcHostGroup.description: A collection of objects providing information for a Switch/Service/Host that implements PVC traps for an ATM interfaces.
